The paper discusses a variant of k-d trees for nearest neighbor search, which is a common topic in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The focus on massively-parallel processing suggests a potential fit for distributed and parallel computing (cs.DC) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). Finally, the application of the modified framework in astronomy suggests a potential fit for numerical analysis (cs.NA).
